accord said in sight in brazil seamen 's strike an accord is in sight in brazil' 20-day-old nation seamen 's strike , which ha serious delay export , a union offici said . the offici , speak from strike headquart in rio de janeiro , said up to 30,000 of brazil 's 40,000 seamen were still on strike . he said the other had return to work over the last week , accept pay offer of 120 pct from four privat compani and from the frota nacion de petroleiro ( fronap ) , part of the state-own oil compani petrobra . the associ group privat shipown , syndarma , ha also offer 120 pct but talk have so far been deadlock over payment for overtim . the union offici said he believ thi issu would be resolv shortli .